cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper discusses the security implications of using outdated JavaScript libraries on websites, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also touches upon issues related to software engineering (cs.SE), programming languages (cs.PL), and cybernetics (cs.CY) in terms of dependency management, code maintenance, and third-party code inclusion. Additionally, the paper uses data analysis and tracking techniques to quantify different scenarios, which could fall under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI).
